Purpose

This document summarizes Rick Gilmores analysis of participant sorting data.

Set-up

Analysis plan

  1. Were there differences in mean Jaccard indices by wallpaper group?

Import data

The Jaccard index data are found in analysis/data/jaccard.csv.

jaccard_df <- readr::read_csv("analysis/data/jaccard.csv")
## 
##  Column specification 
## cols(
##   Exemplar.Row = col_double(),
##   Exemplar.Col = col_double(),
##   Jaccard = col_double(),
##   Group = col_character()
## )

Visualizations

jaccard_plot_1 <- jaccard_df %>%
  ggplot(.) +
  aes(x = Jaccard, fill = Group) +
  geom_histogram() +
  facet_grid(. ~ Group)
jaccard_plot_1
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

jaccard_plot_2 <- jaccard_df %>%
  ggplot(.) +
  aes(x = Jaccard, fill = Group) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  facet_grid(Group ~ .) +
  scale_y_continuous(NULL, breaks = NULL)
jaccard_plot_2

Analyses

Using lm

There are no random effects in this model.

jaccard_lm <- lm(Jaccard ~ Group, data = jaccard_df)
summary(jaccard_lm)
##
